From 1e593ae1ef70d453ebd0755ad94ff2f8c9344c90 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date: Wed, 24 Jun 2026 23:00:35 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Remove date suffixes from file names across all notebooks

Strip date tokens (e.g. _dec20, _oct27, _jan12, _feb7, _feb11, _feb15,
_jan25, _oct16) from every file/directory name, applied uniformly so
producers and consumers stay in sync. No two dated names collapse onto
the same undated name (checked for collisions). This also resolves a
couple of pre-existing mismatches where a producer already wrote the
undated name while a consumer still read the dated one (e.g.
ibd2_all_trimmed_*cM.txt between nb11 and nb13/14/17).

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 <noreply@anthropic.com>
Claude-Session: https://claude.ai/code/session_011xXry1AZa3FkSAuNHDtxKo
